snippet: The owners of the former Victor's Cafe on the Upper West Side have decided to keep a high relief mural that was commissioned in the early '70s instead of tearing it down for a renovation project.

headline.main: A Scene From Cuban Sugarcane Fields Will Endure on Columbus Avenue
